Lene Lovich (born March 30, 1949) is an American born British singer who first 
gained attention as part of the New Wave music scene of the late 1970s and early 
1980s, mostly due to her high-pitched voice, and quirky style and appearance. She 
was one of the pioneers of female punk rock whose most popular hit single was 
"Lucky Number", first released in 1978.
